--- WHAT THIS MEANS IN PLAIN ENGLISH ---

You can:
  - Use Modkit freely, including in commercial Minecraft modpacks
  - Distribute Modkit as part of your modpack
  - Build mods on top of Modkit and license those mods however you want
    (this is the key LGPL distinction — only Modkit itself is LGPL,
    not the mods you create with it)

You must:
  - Keep this license notice when redistributing Modkit itself
  - Make source code of any MODIFICATIONS to Modkit itself available
    if you redistribute a modified version
  - Not relicense Modkit itself under a different license

You may NOT:
  - Claim Modkit as your own work
  - Remove or hide the LGPL notice when redistributing


--- MODS YOU CREATE WITH MODKIT ---

When you click "Export" in Modkit and ship a .jar to other players, that
output jar contains YOUR content (JSON definitions, textures). The license
of THAT mod is whatever you set in the Project Settings of your workspace.

Modkit only acts as a runtime engine — your output mods depend on Modkit
but don't include any of its source code, which is why your mods can be
licensed independently of LGPL.
